77
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:09,160
Didn't I tell you?

78
00:05:09,279 --> 00:05:10,360
It's just routine.

79
00:05:11,319 --> 00:05:13,240
Something really happened at the East Gate.

80
00:05:13,759 --> 00:05:14,920
A group of anti-Japanese activists

81
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,480
killed several of our men.

82
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:17,920
The military police are arresting people right now.

83
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,040
Don't play games with me.

84
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:22,480
Let them arrest whoever they want.

85
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,000
Why are you bothering me?

86
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,319
Are you still suspicious of me?

87
00:05:26,319 --> 00:05:27,680
Who's suspicious of you?

88
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:28,920
It's a joint operation.

89
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,480
Takagi Yuyi has been watching me closely.

90
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,519
How could I not do something?

91
00:05:35,279 --> 00:05:36,160
Anything else?

92
00:05:36,839 --> 00:05:38,439
You could've just sent him to buy the medicine.

93
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:39,920
Why did you come yourself?

94
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,040
If I sent him,

95
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:42,079
do you believe

96
00:05:42,079 --> 00:05:43,800
he'd bring back the whole pharmacy for me?

97
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:45,160
You're right, boss.

98
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:50,720
Take a look.

99
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,680
Is this the one?

100
00:05:58,879 --> 00:05:59,399
Yes.

101
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,240
That's right.

102
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,360
Brother.

103
00:06:01,839 --> 00:06:02,680
You were thoughtful.

104
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,720
As your older brother, I misunderstood you.

105
00:06:05,959 --> 00:06:07,439
Sister-in-law is truly a real sister-in-law.

106
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,319
Brother.

107
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,360
No.

108
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,839
Why are you being so petty?

109
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:12,560
Let's go.

110
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,279
Excuse me.

111
00:06:42,279 --> 00:06:43,279
Just say what you want to say.

112
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,600
Boss, here's the situation.

113
00:06:47,759 --> 00:06:50,079
Just now, Li Delun cornered me against the wall.

114
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,360
He asked me

115
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,199
when I was buying medicine,

116
00:06:52,199 --> 00:06:53,839
if you went with me.

117
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,639
How did you answer?

118
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,879
Of course I said I went with you.

119
00:06:58,399 --> 00:06:59,040
Boss.

120
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:00,519
Even though I was transferred from the General Affairs Department,

121
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:02,040
I'm following you now.

122
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,360
I'm your man.

123
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,360
I know exactly what those people are thinking.

124
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,519
I know it all too well.

125
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,560
Brother Bai and Brother Yu have both told me.

126
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,399
That group from the Intelligence Department

127
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:11,399
those people

128
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,920
just love stirring things up behind the scenes.

129
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:13,959
Yes.

130
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,439
There's nothing wrong with catching anti-Japanese elements.

131
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,399
But you can't just bite whoever you catch.

132
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,759
If I didn't say it this way,

133
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,160
Then wouldn't they be like flies,

134
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,199
buzzing around you nonstop?

135
00:07:24,639 --> 00:07:25,439
Zhao Di.

136
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,240
Boss.

137
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,160
I knew you were clever.

138
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,639
At critical moments,

139
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,279
you always keep a clear head.

140
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,839
It's thanks to your guidance, Boss.

141
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,399
By the way, Boss,

142
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,399
was there a problem with the medicine I bought?

143
00:07:38,519 --> 00:07:40,000
I saw there was still quite a lot left.

144
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,240
The rest have too many side effects.

145
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:45,959
Like this one,

146
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:47,160
pregnant women can't use it.

147
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:49,120
Director Cui and his wife

148
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,759
haven't had a child all these years.

149
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,720
I almost caused trouble.

150
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,800
So Director Cui must be

151
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:57,600
pretty sensitive about this.

152
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,360
Yeah.

153
00:08:00,199 --> 00:08:01,160
So,

154
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,160
be even more careful and smart.

155
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,319
Got it, Boss.

156
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,120
We're here.

157
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,879
Just now at the teahouse,

158
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:23,360
who was the one who gave the warning?

159
00:08:23,759 --> 00:08:24,720
Why did they do that?

160
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,240
I'm not sure either.

161
00:08:26,959 --> 00:08:28,000
But I heard

162
00:08:28,319 --> 00:08:29,120
he's a Communist.

163
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,240
These two agents

164
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,679
were taken out at the chaotic scene.

165
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,159
That could be overlooked.

166
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,000
But as for the other two people,

167
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,320
it's obvious

168
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,960
that it was done by someone they knew.

169
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,679
Did no one else at the scene

170
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:52,039
notice anything at all?

171
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:54,559
The situation is more complicated than we thought.

172
00:08:54,799 --> 00:08:56,480
Our people, in such a short time,

173
00:08:56,559 --> 00:08:58,159
couldn't make thorough arrangements.

174
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,519
A lack of manpower

175
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:01,159
is certainly part of the reason.

176
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:03,399
But such a tiny wound

177
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,919
is quite rare.

178
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:07,000
I think

179
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,360
you should consider this angle

180
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,360
and think about it.

181
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,559
At our headquarters,

182
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,399
who exactly

183
00:09:13,399 --> 00:09:15,960
has used a dagger of this shape?

184
00:09:20,279 --> 00:09:21,159
Director Li

185
00:09:21,759 --> 00:09:22,519
I think

186
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,440
this morning

187
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,360
all personnel who left the Special Agent Headquarters

188
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,159
should undergo a unified screening

189
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,120
I want to know

190
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,879
who is actually suspected of committing the crime

191
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,039
Mr. Takagi

192
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:34,200
The Peace Conference is just around the corner

193
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,720
There has been a lot of personnel going out

