214
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:20,840
Very good

215
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:22,159
You may leave

216
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,600
Do I need to repeat myself?

217
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:28,399
Yes

218
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:39,919
Mr. Takagi

219
00:10:40,159 --> 00:10:41,200
Just based on this

220
00:10:41,759 --> 00:10:43,080
can you figure anything out?

221
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,840
As long as you pay attention,

222
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:47,279
of course you can find something.

223
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:50,480
Then, Mr. Takagi,

224
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,519
please give us your guidance.

225
00:10:52,279 --> 00:10:54,240
These materials seem complicated,

226
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,080
but actually,

227
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,840
most people can be ruled out.

228
00:10:59,279 --> 00:11:01,320
At the crime scene, you also saw

229
00:11:01,639 --> 00:11:02,759
that the two No. 76 agents

230
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:04,159
were killed by someone they knew.

231
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:06,159
Think about it:

232
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,720
what kind of person

233
00:11:08,279 --> 00:11:09,159
could make two

234
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:11,440
agents already on duty

