292
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:07,240
I was just running errands for Director Li.

293
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,600
Aside from work-related tasks,

294
00:14:08,679 --> 00:14:10,080
I didn't go anywhere else.

295
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:11,919
Is that so?

296
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,360
As far as I know,

297
00:14:13,559 --> 00:14:15,960
it takes less than thirty minutes on foot

298
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:18,399
from the Special Operations Headquarters to your destination.

299
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:20,559
You left at eight o'clock

300
00:14:20,919 --> 00:14:23,559
and didn't return until 11:02.

301
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,039
About this,

302
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,919
don't you want to explain?

303
00:14:27,639 --> 00:14:28,440
I...

304
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,320
You don't need to worry.

305
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,679
I can understand

306
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,360
that outside of work,

307
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,000
you might take care of some personal matters.

308
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,799
But you must find

309
00:14:37,799 --> 00:14:40,320
someone who can confirm where you went.

310
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,399
Otherwise,

311
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:45,320
I will charge you with treason.

312
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:47,039
Do you understand?

313
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:48,200
Understood.

314
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:53,720
Alright.

315
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:54,840
Take him out.

316
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:02,080
I've already explained everything I needed to.

317
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:04,039
Mr. Takagi, do you have any other questions?

318
00:15:06,039 --> 00:15:07,799
With Director Cui as your witness,

319
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:09,679
there shouldn't be any issues, of course.

320
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,200
But I still want to remind Director Liang

321
00:15:13,039 --> 00:15:14,919
to pay more attention to the people around you.

322
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,120
The people around me?

323
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:21,120
If this is just your speculation, Chief Takagi,

324
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,720
then let's just drop it.

325
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:24,840
I also want to catch the infiltrator as soon as possible.

326
00:15:25,279 --> 00:15:27,000
That way, I can devote more energy

327
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,759
to my unfinished work

328
00:15:29,159 --> 00:15:31,320
instead of sitting here making small talk.

329
00:15:35,679 --> 00:15:36,600
Damn it.

330
00:15:46,039 --> 00:15:47,240
Basically, everyone

331
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,080
has a legitimate reason.

332
00:15:49,279 --> 00:15:50,159
Mr. Takagi,

333
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,960
the direction of our investigation

334
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,559
might have some issues.

335
00:15:54,279 --> 00:15:57,200
Problems are always found in the details.

336
00:15:58,960 --> 00:15:59,919
No need to rush.

337
00:16:00,519 --> 00:16:02,039
We will definitely find something.

338
00:16:02,519 --> 00:16:03,879
The main issue is time.

339
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:06,000
The Peace Conference delegates

340
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,159
will soon be heading to Shanghai.

341
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:09,200
If we try to root out anti-Japanese elements at this time,

342
00:16:09,519 --> 00:16:11,080
I'm afraid we won't find anyone

343
00:16:11,559 --> 00:16:13,120
before the Peace Conference has already started.

344
00:16:17,799 --> 00:16:18,639
I heard

345
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:21,519
Director Cui and Director Liang are quite close personally.

346
00:16:21,799 --> 00:16:22,600
Not really.

347
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:24,320
We've just known each other for a long time.

348
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,080
Hirata Noriko investigated him before.

349
00:16:28,639 --> 00:16:29,919
That was just a misunderstanding.

350
00:16:30,879 --> 00:16:32,120
Before Hirata had her incident,

351
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:34,159
Liang Shuo started dating a new girlfriend.

352
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:35,159
Yes.

353
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,559
I even monitored her.

354
00:16:36,679 --> 00:16:37,639
But later on,

355
00:16:37,639 --> 00:16:38,679
she was cleared of suspicion.

356
00:16:42,639 --> 00:16:43,440
Director Cui,

357
00:16:44,039 --> 00:16:45,279
being thorough is a good thing.

358
00:16:45,279 --> 00:16:46,639
It's commendable.

359
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,360
But I suggest

360
00:16:48,519 --> 00:16:49,759
keeping work and personal matters separate.

361
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:50,919
Personal matters

362
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:51,960
should be handled privately.

363
00:16:53,159 --> 00:16:54,080
Mr. Takagi,

364
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,679
is that really necessary?

365
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:57,679
That depends on how you see it.

366
00:17:01,039 --> 00:17:01,600
Please,

367
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:22,519
come in.

368
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,240
Cui, what brings you here today?

369
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,759
It's really busy.

370
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,200
Busy, busy.

371
00:17:36,039 --> 00:17:37,400
Both annoying and busy.

372
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:38,720
Look here.

373
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,200
Coordinating accommodations for the new government delegates.

374
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,839
Security patrol routes.

375
00:17:44,319 --> 00:17:46,599
Managing and controlling the surrounding traffic.

376
00:17:46,799 --> 00:17:47,680
And this, too.

377
00:17:47,759 --> 00:17:48,640
The hardest part is

378
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:50,319
the household registration investigation.

379
00:17:50,599 --> 00:17:51,880
All the tenants in the area

380
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,519
have to be cleared out.

381
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:55,119
The team assigned to me

382
00:17:55,119 --> 00:17:56,559
is just two police stations.

383
00:17:57,759 --> 00:17:59,599
You can't make a meal without rice.

384
00:17:59,599 --> 00:18:01,079
I'm about ready to give up.

385
00:18:01,759 --> 00:18:03,200
And then there's Takagi from the military police.

386
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,200
He keeps coming to cause me trouble.

387
00:18:05,759 --> 00:18:07,559
It was never this big of a deal before.

388
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:08,839
Looks like this time

389
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,400
they really mean business.

390
00:18:10,799 --> 00:18:12,319
You said that was before.

391
00:18:16,599 --> 00:18:17,400
Brother Cui,

392
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:18,680
if you really want to see,

393
00:18:18,839 --> 00:18:19,799
I'll show you.

394
00:18:20,119 --> 00:18:22,000
I've been looking for someone to take the blame for me.

395
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,440
That was a great reminder.

396
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,319
I almost forgot.

397
00:18:29,319 --> 00:18:31,440
You're now Director Liang of the Special Investigation Department.

398
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:33,039
If I look at your department's files,

399
00:18:33,039 --> 00:18:34,000
that would be a breach of protocol.

400
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,119
You'd better put them away quickly.

401
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,279
Yeah.

402
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,119
In our line of work,

403
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,799
the more you know, the more trouble you get into.

404
00:18:42,279 --> 00:18:43,160
You came at just the right time.

405
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,240
Saves me the trouble of looking for you.

406
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:46,160
Director Liang.

407
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,400
Do you have any instructions?

408
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:49,640
Stop joking around.

409
00:18:52,759 --> 00:18:55,000
Someone from the Special Committee just called.

410
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,440
They asked about the Xiaodongmen incident.

411
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:57,359
Any leads yet?

412
00:18:57,359 --> 00:18:58,400
It's not that fast.

413
00:18:58,599 --> 00:18:59,640
It's only been a day.

414
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,880
I'm not some kind of super detective.

415
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,200
Also,

416
00:19:02,599 --> 00:19:03,480
Since when does the Special Committee

417
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,200
get involved in such minor matters?

418
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,720
It's not exactly a minor matter.

419
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,960
Nanjing takes this very seriously.

420
00:19:11,839 --> 00:19:12,759
You know,

421
00:19:13,359 --> 00:19:14,440
those officials

422
00:19:14,559 --> 00:19:15,799
have long been scared

423
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,079
by the Communists and the Chongqing faction.

424
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,720
They're terrified.

425
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,079
The higher-ups just say a word,

426
00:19:22,759 --> 00:19:24,119
and the people below run themselves ragged.

427
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,640
I don't see you running yourself ragged.

428
00:19:27,839 --> 00:19:28,720
You still have the leisure

429
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,079
to come chat with me.

430
00:19:30,359 --> 00:19:32,440
Can't I come see you for personal reasons?

431
00:19:32,799 --> 00:19:33,599
Personal reasons?

432
00:19:34,359 --> 00:19:35,359
Your sister-in-law asked me

433
00:19:35,359 --> 00:19:36,480
to check on Miss Xie's health.

434
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:37,359
How is her recovery going?

435
00:19:37,359 --> 00:19:38,279
If she's better,

436
00:19:38,279 --> 00:19:39,160
let's find a time

437
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,400
to have a meal at home.

438
00:19:41,279 --> 00:19:42,079
That's all?

439
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,359
What do you mean, "that's all"?

440
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,440
Why "that's all"?

441
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:45,680
This is an order from our family's highest authority.

442
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:46,799
It's a direct instruction.

443
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,240
You must have time for a family meal.

444
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,000
Surely you can spare that.

445
00:19:50,759 --> 00:19:52,039
Please, give me a break.

446
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:53,079
Can't you see

447
00:19:53,079 --> 00:19:54,680
I've got a mess to deal with here?

448
00:19:54,839 --> 00:19:55,759
That's not my concern.

449
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,960
I'm just passing on the order.

450
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:58,960
So, what do you say?

451
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:03,680
Alright.

452
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:04,799
When?

453
00:20:04,839 --> 00:20:05,720
Tonight.

454
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,559
It's settled, then.

455
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:33,839
You startled me.

456
00:20:34,119 --> 00:20:35,559
I thought I got on the wrong car.

457
00:20:36,359 --> 00:20:37,400
Did I scare you?

458
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,079
You look different from usual.

459
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:47,720
Do I look good?

460
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,039
Not bad.

461
00:20:52,519 --> 00:20:53,400
Not bad.

462
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,680
I thought since today is Director Cui's family dinner,

463
00:20:56,799 --> 00:20:58,200
you shouldn't feel too restrained.

464
00:20:58,519 --> 00:20:59,720
Just relax a bit.

465
00:21:07,119 --> 00:21:10,000
Leave it to Feiman.

466
00:21:10,559 --> 00:21:11,920
Are you free in the next few days?

467
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,000
Let's go watch a movie together.

468
00:21:14,799 --> 00:21:16,480
Are there any good movies lately?

469
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:17,799
Zhao Di.

470
00:21:18,039 --> 00:21:19,240
Any good movies recently?

471
00:21:19,519 --> 00:21:20,519
Mulan Joins the Army.

472
00:21:20,599 --> 00:21:22,079
Miss Chen Yunshang's new film.

473
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,519
I heard it's pretty good.

474
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,000
There's also that one that was released earlier,

475
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,680
the romantic tragedy.

476
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:27,359
The Beautiful Lady Yu.

477
00:21:27,359 --> 00:21:28,119
It's been re-released recently.

478
00:21:29,559 --> 00:21:30,519
Then,

479
00:21:31,079 --> 00:21:32,119
let's watch Mulan Joins the Army.

480
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:33,720
I'm not going.

481
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,279
Why?

482
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:36,599
It's a last-minute invitation.

483
00:21:36,599 --> 00:21:37,839
You're really not sincere.

484
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,519
You finally made it.

485
00:22:06,079 --> 00:22:06,880
Brother Cui.

486
00:22:07,839 --> 00:22:08,279
Come on in.

487
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:09,920
Big Brother Cui.

488
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:10,599
Sister-in-law.

489
00:22:10,599 --> 00:22:11,319
Welcome.

490
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,559
How is your recovery going?

491
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:14,759
Thank you for your concern, Big Brother Cui.

492
00:22:14,759 --> 00:22:15,599
Much better.

493
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,640
The illness came quickly but went away just as fast.

494
00:22:17,839 --> 00:22:18,960
You need to take care and recuperate.

495
00:22:19,039 --> 00:22:19,920
You can't let it relapse.

496
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:21,640
By the way,

497
00:22:21,799 --> 00:22:23,000
since I'm coming to your house,

498
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,000
I brought a gift for you and your wife.

499
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:25,839
Director Cui,

500
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:28,880
ever since you got married,

501
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,200
you've really become thoughtful.

502
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:30,960
When you used to come to my house before,

503
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:32,400
you wouldn't even bring a single peanut.

504
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,200
Where's your wife?

505
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,480
She's in the kitchen.

506
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,440
She knew you were coming,

507
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,279
and nagged me all day.

508
00:22:37,279 --> 00:22:38,079
It drove me crazy.

509
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,720
Your wife is cooking herself?

510
00:22:40,079 --> 00:22:40,920
Then I have to go order some dishes.

511
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:41,359
Let's go.

512
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,799
What's going on?

513
00:22:43,799 --> 00:22:45,720
Your collar is all messed up, one side in front and one in back.

514
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,599
You should pay more attention.

515
00:22:46,599 --> 00:22:47,319
Sister-in-law,

516
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,160
you can't be too nice to him.

517
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,519
You'll spoil him.

518
00:22:51,599 --> 00:22:51,960
Let's go.

519
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:52,440
Please.

520
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:58,359
Sir, you're back.

521
00:22:58,559 --> 00:22:59,880
Hello, Mr. Liang, hello.

522
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:00,599
Hello.

523
00:23:01,079 --> 00:23:02,319
Sister-in-law, we're here.

524
00:23:02,559 --> 00:23:03,359
Hello, Miss.

525
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:04,799
You're already here.

526
00:23:04,799 --> 00:23:06,759
I thought you wouldn't arrive so soon.

527
00:23:07,799 --> 00:23:08,319
Thank you.

528
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,160
This must be Miss Xie.

529
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:10,920
Sir.

530
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:11,759
Hello.

531
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,519
I've introduced you to so many well-known ladies.

532
00:23:14,519 --> 00:23:16,160
How come you didn't like any of them?

533
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:18,200
Now I finally understand.

534
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:21,240
Miss Xie is really beautiful.

535
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,640
Our Liang Shuo is truly lucky.

536
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,240
Sister-in-law, you're too kind.

537
00:23:25,839 --> 00:23:26,759
Come, tell me quickly.

538
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:27,960
How did you two meet?

539
00:23:30,319 --> 00:23:31,400
The kitchen is a woman's place.

540
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:32,359
Why are you joining in?

541
00:23:32,359 --> 00:23:32,680
Come.

542
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:33,359
Sit over here.

543
00:23:34,519 --> 00:23:36,759
I can tell sister-in-law is really happy today.

544
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:37,960
During this time,

545
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:39,640
you probably haven't spent much time with her.

546
00:23:44,559 --> 00:23:45,640
Actually, we're all the same.

547
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,200
Sometimes,

548
00:23:47,839 --> 00:23:49,440
we don't even know what we're doing.

549
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,359
Cat's way, dog's way,

550
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:55,200
as long as we survive, it's a good way.

551
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:58,680
I remember Brother Cui said that, right?

552
00:23:59,839 --> 00:24:00,920
People like us,

553
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:02,119
wearing this dog's skin,

554
00:24:02,119 --> 00:24:03,160
what is it all for?

555
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:06,000
Isn't it just for

556
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,000
letting our families have a good life?

557
00:24:09,279 --> 00:24:10,400
Brother Cui, let me tell you,

558
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:11,960
this Xiao Xie,

559
00:24:12,559 --> 00:24:13,759
I really like her.

560
00:24:19,559 --> 00:24:20,599
I knew you were coming.

561
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,640
Your sister-in-law has been busy from morning till night.

562
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,880
Alright, time to eat.

563
00:24:26,039 --> 00:24:28,240
I made a lot of local dishes.

564
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:30,319
That's amazing.

565
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,640
Thank you for your hard work, sister-in-law.

566
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,799
How come you never say I work hard?

567
00:24:35,079 --> 00:24:36,240
You worked hard too.

568
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,880
We're the worst for just coming to eat for free.

569
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,480
That's true.

570
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:43,000
Sister-in-law, I really like your personality.

571
00:24:43,039 --> 00:24:44,680
You're witty, humorous, lively, and adorable.

572
00:24:45,119 --> 00:24:46,599
It's been a long time since I cooked.

573
00:24:46,599 --> 00:24:48,799
We also have to thank Miss for helping out as a guest.

574
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:50,279
I really feel embarrassed.

575
00:24:50,319 --> 00:24:51,519
